In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for
4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with @Sriracha{1%tsp}
to taste.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz} and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook,
breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @shredded carrots{4%oz}, @sesame dressing{1.5%oz}, 2 1/2 TBSP
@sweet soy glaze{2 1/2%tbsp} (5 TBSP for 4 servings), and @sugar{1/2%tsp}
(1 tsp for 4). Cook until carrots are softened, pork is cooked through,
and sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Taste and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP
for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with pork mixture and any remaining
sauce from pan. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo. Sprinkle with
@crispy fried onions{1} and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.